  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Youth, Violence and Crime in Sierra Leone</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">After Ebola, over 60 % of youth are now unemployed in Sierra Leone. Many are currently at risk to violence and crime perpetuated by organised cliques/gangs in fragile cities in Sierra Leone. Change needs to happen within local communities or  &quot;Hot Spots areas&quot;. This project will train community youth leaders to effectively design and organise Dialogue Forums aimed at understanding the root causes, the recruitment patterns and priority needs of youth associated with cliques/gang in Sierra Leone.</narrative>
  </description>
